x4freetext: English translation
Isochronous 103-cm cyclotron
The measurements of continuous excitation functions
were made with 4 movable detectors set in thirteen
laboratory angles, at 170, and 160-124 degr. in steps
of 3 and 4 degr., and using a fixed monitor at -20
degr.
The authors used thick-target method which was
based on the ideas of backscattering element analysis.
The 14C targets, enriched to 71% in 14C, were thick
enough only to degrade the beam energy by 100 keV
when tilted by 45 degr. with respect to the beam
direction.
